stories.text: Authoritarian regimes control the media and block internet access to unwanted web sites. This prevents citizens from gaining access to at least other viewpoints than the political propaganda. To combat this, would it be possible to go on public transport and open a free WiFi hotspot where people can download, say, Wikipedia and PDFs of the latest headlines of independent news outlets, ideally translated into the local language?
stories.title: Ask HN: "Newsbombs" as a way to combat authoritarian propaganda?
